Reference-contexts: V. CONCLUSION AND FUTURE WORKS We believe that RSVP message delivery mechanism requires some degree of reliability guarantee. One way of improving reliability is to grant some minimal bandwidth for RSVP messages to protect them from congestion losses, as being suggested in Reference <ref> [2] </ref>. However it may require additional functions at both sending and receiving nodes. And it is not clear how it can be backward compatible. In this paper, we presented a mechanism that enhances the current RSVP message delivery and is completely backward compatible.
